\# Sustainable Fashion Survey Data Analysis 👗📊

This project analyzes data from a fashion consumer survey using Microsoft Excel. It involves cleaning raw data, generating pivot tables for insights, and creating a visual dashboard.

\#\# 📁 Project Contents

\- \*\*Original Data\*\*: Raw survey responses  
\- \*\*Cleaned Data\*\*: Categorized values like age groups, gender, shopping frequency, and platform discovery  
\- \*\*Pivot Tables\*\*: Aggregated insights (platform vs country, style preference vs age, etc.)  
\- \*\*Dashboard\*\*: Charts created from the pivot tables for easy visualization

\#\# 📊 Charts and Analysis

\- 📌 Count of platform usage per country (Bar Chart)  
\- 🎯 Discovery methods (Online/Offline) summarized  
\- 💡 Sustainable fashion knowledge levels (Grouped)  
\- 🕵️ Style type preferences vs. demographics

\#\# 🧰 Tools Used

\- Microsoft Excel  
\- Pivot Tables  
\- Data Cleaning  
\- Charts (Bar, Pie, Line)

\#\# ✨ Key Insights

\- Online platforms dominate in urban areas  
\- Gen Z prefers trendy styles; older groups lean toward timeless fashion  
\- Sustainable knowledge scores range between 2–7, with most responses between 4–6
